rity of SiIII-selected absorbers in our sample trace the CGM of nearby\ngalaxies within their virial radii at a typical covering fraction of ~70 per\ncent. From a detailed ionization model we estimate that diffuse gas in the CGM\naround galaxies, as traced by SiIII, contains substantially more baryonic mass\nthan their neutral interstellar medium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Jul 2015 20:00:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Mar 2016 12:27:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-18"}
